Citation.sAbstract: Air liquid interfacial surface tension measurements are reported on four 1-alkyl-3-methylimidazolium  ([Cn-mim], n = 2, 4, 6) based ionic liquids at 15 temperatures from (283 to 353) K at atmospheric pressure.  To validate the accuracy of the results, the Wilhelmy plate method and the du Nouy ring method were  employed in parallel, using the Kr}uss K100MK2 tensiometer. At each temperature from 29 to 44 individual  readings were taken. The surface tension average values at particular temperatures are presented  with the estimated overall standard uncertainty ranging from (+-0.025 to +-0.1) mN   m 1. An empirical  surface tension temperature equation has been developed describing the temperature dependence of  each ionic liquid surface tension. Some details of the measurement procedure that have been found to  be important in achieving the highest possible accuracy are discussed.
Citation.sTitle: Surface tension measurements with validated accuracy for four 1-alkyl-3-methylimidazolium based ionic liquids
